description: I took this photo many years ago, but it is a noteworthy enough plant observation to be added to iNaturalist retroactively. There are very few records of this species from San Francisco and no specimens collected since 1962. Only days after taking this photo, the plants (5 in all) had been apparently eaten - nothing remained but holes where the roots had been.

A quick snap of a wildflower in the San Gabriel Mtns -- I'd just gotten my old camera & was trying it out.  This species was common there, but I'd never been able to identify it until now.  Turns out it's because it's got a very restricted range, endemic to Southern California and found mainly in the Transverse Ranges.  Not a great photo, but figured it was worth posting given that there isn't a single other tagged example on Flickr.
